// engine-010-history — `history` attribute on a composite state-child (§51.0.N).
//
// Demonstrates A5-7 history surface (S67 amendment, SPEC §51.0.N) — a bare
// `history` attribute on a composite state-child instructs the compiler to
// synthesize a reactive cell that stores the inner engine's last-active
// variant on outer-exit, and restores from that cell on outer-re-entry.
//
// Target form `.Variant.history` (§51.0.N): used wherever `.Variant` is legal
// as a `rule=` target or as the right-hand side of an engine-variable write,
// to mean "transition AND restore inner from history" (vs bare `.Variant`
// which starts the inner at its initial=).
//
// `history` is legal ONLY on composite state-children (those whose body
// contains a nested <engine>). On a non-composite state-child the typer fires
// E-HISTORY-NO-INNER-ENGINE per §34. Shallow only this revision per
// OQ-Harel-4 — deep history is deferred.
//
// v1 implementation state (2026-05-11, post-Bug-3 / Wave 2.3 ship):
//   - Parser captures `historyAttr: true` (engine-statechild-parser.ts).
//   - Parser captures `.Variant.history` as `historyForm: true` on rule entries.
//   - Typer (SYM PASS 11) fires E-HISTORY-NO-INNER-ENGINE on non-composite.
//   - Codegen (emit-engine.ts, A5-7 Wave 2.3, Bug #3) SHIPPED 2026-05-11:
//       * Per-engine `__scrml_engine_<varName>_history_map` const recording
//         {outerVariant → innerEngineVarName} for each composite state-child
//         that carries `history`.
//       * Per-state-child synth-cell init lines:
//         `_scrml_state["_<outerVar>_<scTag>_history"] = null;`
//         (empty-history fallback per §51.0.N — first-entry case).
//       * historyMap threaded as 7th positional arg to
//         `_scrml_engine_direct_set` / `_scrml_engine_advance`.
//       * Runtime helper `_scrml_engine_history_capture_on_exit`
//         (runtime-template.js) captures inner-engine variant into the synth
//         cell on EXTERNAL outer-exit when current !== target (real exit,
//         not self-loop). Internal transitions (§51.0.O) bypass the capture
//         by construction — the internal branch of the runtime helpers
//         returns false without touching history.
//   - Transitions table still flattens `.X.history → "X"`: the `.history`
//     suffix doesn't change which targets are legal — only the entry
//     semantics, which the WRITE site drives (not the rule= legality table).
//   - Restore-on-re-entry observable verification deferred to Bug #2
//     (Wave 2.4 — inner-engine dispatcher emission). The synth-cell
//     write/read MECHANISM is fully wired this dispatch; the observable
//     inner-engine restore-from-cell requires Bug #2's inner-engine
//     dispatcher to mount on outer re-entry.
//   - Tree-shake (§51.0.N): when no engine declares `history`, NO history-
//     map const, NO synth cells, NO write-guard historyArg emit. Zero-byte
//     cost for non-history engines.
//
// Note on the buttons in this sample: `onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Playing}`
// currently routes through the event-handler shortcut path which bypasses
// `_scrml_engine_direct_set` (pre-existing — Bug #6 / Wave 2.5 territory).
// History capture fires through `.advance()` calls and function-body writes;
// it will also fire through onclick once Bug #6 routes those through the
// engine write-guard.

<program>
${
    type AppMode:enum  = { Title, Playing, Paused }
    type PlayMode:enum = { Exploring, Battle, Inventory }
}

<engine for=AppMode initial=.Title>
    <Title rule=.Playing></>

    <Playing history rule=(.Title | .Paused)>
        <engine for=PlayMode initial=.Exploring>
            <Exploring rule=.Battle></>
            <Battle rule=.Exploring></>
            <Inventory></>
        </>
    </>

    <Paused rule=.Playing.history></>
</>

<div class="game">
    <h1>App: ${@appMode.variant}</>
    <button onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Playing}>Start</>
    <button onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Paused}>Pause</>
    <button onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Title}>Quit</>
</div>
</program>
